# loom

A terminal-based agentic coding assistant. Give it a natural-language task,
and it reads/edits files, runs shell commands, and searches your project —
iterating until the job is done.

## Install (dev)

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

Requires Python 3.11+.

## Setup

Set your Anthropic API key:

```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-...
```

Or add `api_key` to `~/.loom/config.toml`:

```toml
api_key = "sk-..."
model = "claude-sonnet-4-6"
permission_mode = "confirm"   # confirm | yolo | deny
```

## Usage

```bash
loom "read main.py and tell me what it does"
loom --yolo "refactor utils.py to use pathlib"
loom --resume <session_id> "continue where we left off"
loom sessions          # list past sessions
```

### Options

- `--yolo` — skip permission prompts (still blocked by the safety denylist)
- `--resume <id>` — reload a previous session's history
- `--model <name>` — override the model
- `--no-stream` — disable live streaming

## Tools the agent can use

- `read_file`, `write_file`, `edit_file` — file operations
- `bash` — run shell commands (with timeout)
- `glob`, `grep` — search the project

## Safety

Before any write or shell action, `loom` prompts for confirmation (unless
`--yolo`). A hard denylist blocks obviously destructive commands (e.g.
`rm -rf /`, fork bombs) regardless of mode.

## Architecture

```
loom/
  cli.py          typer entry point
  agent/          LangGraph loop, prompts, state
  tools/          file / shell / search tools + executor
  session/        SQLite persistence + project tree
  ui/             rich rendering + permission prompts
  config.py       config loading
```

## Tests

```bash
pytest
```
